Package com.vectorprint.report.itext.style.stylers

Parametrizable classes responsible for styling.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Advanced<DATATYPE>
    An advanced styler is a styler that is meant to draw directly on the canvas as opposed to regular stylers that only configure elements later to be added to the document.
  • Class Summary

Package com.vectorprint.report.itext.style.stylers Description

Parametrizable classes responsible for styling. Styling can be done through configuration or from code. Most stylers just set properties of elements, some as well create elements and some create an image and use a helper for turning external formats (svg, chart) into pdf images.
